TY  - JOUR
T1  - Efficiency of Large Double Auctions
AU  - Cripps, Martin W.
AU  - Swinkels, Jeroen M.
Y1  - 2006/01/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00649.x
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 47
EP  - 92
VL  - 74
IS  - 1
KW  - Double auction
KW  - efficiency
KW  - market microstructure
KW  - asymmetric information
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2006.00649.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We consider large double auctions with private values. Values need be neither symmetric nor independent. Multiple units may be owned or desired. Participation may be stochastic. We introduce a very mild notion of ?a little independence.? We prove that all nontrivial equilibria of auctions that satisfy this notion are asymptotically efficient. For any α>0, inefficiency disappears at rate 1/n2-α.
ER  - 

